    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <head>86. Memorandum of a Telephone Conversation Between the <gloss type="from"
                        >Director of the Office of International Financial</gloss> and Development
                    Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_CJC1" type="to">Corbett</persName>) and <persName
                        corresp="#p_RAM2" type="to">Alexander M. Rosenson</persName> of the Office
                    of Regional American Affairs, Washington, April 27, 1956<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d86fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                        820.14/4–2756. Official Use Only. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_RAM2"
                            >Rosenson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1956-04-27">April 27,
                            1956</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_EXIMBankEximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> Loans to Latin
                        American Central Banks</item>
                </list>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CJC1">Corbett</persName> called me in response to my
                    follow-up to him yesterday on this subject.</p>
                <p>He said he had spoken about it to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SWC1"
                        >Sauer</persName>. The latter had told him that there is a division in the
                    Export-Import Bank Board on this matter, some of the Board members favoring the
                    idea, others being opposed to it. The matter has been “kicked around” in an
                    informal manner but up until now the pressure of other business has not
                    permitted a full-fledged policy discussion. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CJC1"
                        >Corbett</persName> informed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SWC1"
                        >Sauer</persName> that the Department is still very much interested in this
                    proposal. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SWC1">Sauer</persName> indicated that it had
                    not been shelved and is still a live issue.</p>
            </div>
